Description: Foot and wall sherd of East Greek pottery bowl or cup; eight-petal star painted on floor with black band further out; exterior reserved with brown band on lower wall; foot and underside reserved; inscriptions cut on exterior and painted under foot.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 312)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 669, no. 273)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.207)
